<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-010-195 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 560 958</DOCID><JOURNAL>EDGE: Work-Group Computing Report  Nov 18 1991 v2 n78 p44(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT EDGE Publishing 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Financial: Western Micro Technology Q3 results.andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Western Micro Technology Inc. (Finance).andO;Ticker:    WSTM.andO;Topic:     Third QuarterLossesFinancial ReportReorganization.andO;Feature:   illustrationtable.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>FINANCIAL: WESTERN MICRO TECHNOLOGY Q3 RESULTSandM;Western Micro Technology, Inc. reported sales of $21,942,000 for the thirdquarter of 1991, ended Sept. 30, 1991, compared with $19,246,000 for thecorresponding quarter a year earlier, an increase of 14 percent.andM;The net loss for the quarter was $2,199,000, equivalent to $.79 per share.andO;For the corresponding quarter a year ago, the net loss was $850,000 or $.30per share.andM;For the nine months ended Sept. 30, 1991, sales were $65,987,000, an increaseof 8 percent from $61,109,000 recorded a year earlier.andP;  The net loss was$2,694,000, or $.97 per share.andP;  For the corresponding nine months a year ago,net loss was $1,629,000, or $.57 per share.andM;Commenting on the results, Marshall G. Cox, Chairman and Chief ExecutiveOfficer of Western Micro Technology, Inc. stated, &quot;Our third quarter loss wasprimarily a result of the recently announced restructuring which is aimed atquickly returning to profitability.andP;  Western Micro will return to a focus onour profitable, historical core businesses of distribution of electronicscomponents/systems and memory testing.andM;&quot;We are eliminating our memory module and cable assembly businesses, whichhave been a drain on profits for over two years.andP;  The restructuring,effective for the third quarter, as well as other miscellaneous one-timecharges, entails a write-off of $1,800,000 and a reduction in personnel ofapproximately 10 percent of all employees.&quot;andM;Western Micro Technology, Inc. is a leading full service electronicdistributor specializing in components and systems products.andP;  The companyalso offers memory and logic testing, burn-in facilities and integration ofcomputer systems.andM;Western Micro Technology, Inc. is headquartered in Saratoga, California withbranches in San Diego, Agoura Hills, and Orange, Calif.; Beaverton, Ore;Redmond, Wash.; Burlington, Mass.; Marlton, N.J.; and reliability testing inDurham, N.C.andO;</TEXT></DOC>